post_text:
In order to celebrate and honor Bridgeport Public School’s Class of 2020, the school will be taking part in the #BeTheLight campaign. On Friday, May 8 at 8:20 PM (2020 military time) the lights of the football field will be turned on for 20 minutes to honor our seniors. The date was chosen because it is the evening before what would have been the previously scheduled graduation. We ask that you drive by safely and remain in your vehicle to view our seniors banners and honk your horn to show support.
It’s a GREAT day to be a Bulldog! #bpsbulldogpride

post_text: Time to brighten up your home and get outside while supporting Bridgeport FFA
shared_text:
Bridgeport Ffa Chapter
April 17 at 10:13 AM ·

We will be opening May 1. We will be open every Friday, Saturday, Sunday, and Monday in May. We will be open from 10am-6pm on these days. We are limiting the number of people in the greenhouse at one time. We will post a sign on our door to let you know if it gets too full. If it gets too full we will ask that you wait in your vehicle. We will also be offering delivery in town only and also curbside pickup. To do this please email bridgeportffagreenhouse@gmail.com for a price sheet and inventory and then send your order in. The price list and inventory will not be sent out till May 1. On your email Please leave your name and number so we can get ahold of you. We will be accepting credit or debit cards this year. If you are able to shop in store please do as we only have so much help. Please Share!

post_text: Some more information on some postponements to this point: Effective Monday, March 16 all NSAA activity practices are suspended until Monday, March 30 and all NSAA activity competitions are suspended until Thursday, April 2. These suspensions may be extended should the conditions warrant. Prom-postponed. All SPVA Activities are cancelled through April 24th. WTC Quiz Bowl scheduled to be held at Morrill has been postponed to a date TBD. Kindergarten registration postponed to a later date. More info to come. Even in these trying times... It’s always a GREAT day to be a Bulldog! #bulldogstogether addition: lions Club sight and hearing screening cancelled for March 23rd.

post_text:
After learning about Viking Longships and citing textual evidence to refute the claim that all Vikings were cruel and ruthless plunderers, Rodak’s 6B students designed and built their own boats with recycled materials and custom- designed sails.

The boats were tested in the water tray and assessed against the success criteria. Awards were given out for best use of resources, best technical expertise, best visual effects, best individual work, and most stable boat. It’s a GREAT day to be a Bulldog! #bpsbulldogpride

“I joined because the Guard lets me serve my country and pursue my passion, wrestling.”⁣
⁣
Casey Benavides is a senior at Bridgeport High School and enlisted an Indirect Fire Infantryman. ⁣
⁣
We want to congratulate him on an amazing wrestling career! Get another W at districts! ⁣
⁣
#GuardTheGoodLife #Wrestling #RoadToState
